request_text: With regard to the genome sequence titled "GenBank NC045512", defined by GenBank as "severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 isolate Whuhan-Hu-1, complete genome", and referenced by the CDC publication "Emerging Infectious Diseases" Volume 26, Number 6, June 2020, titled "Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus 2 from Patient with Coronavirus Disease, United States", I am respectfully requesting any records in possession, custody or control of the CDC which indicate the following: Records which describe the exact or the approximate number of unaltered consecutive nucleotide sequences found in PCR cultures, as a percentage of the total genome size of 29,903. This number or percentage would exclude sequences derived by all other means including: - insertion of GenBank reference sequences - sequences derived by computer algorithms - consensus by panel. I am not requesting records which compare two or more genomes, but rather, what portion of the 29,903 nucleotides which make up the NC045512 genome, represents unaltered nucleotide sequences as observed in the PCR amplicons. If no specific records for this data exist, an approximation by a CDC expert, with a brief explanation of the ratio, as a number or percentage, will suffice. (Date Range for Record Search: From 12/01/2019 To 01/08/2021). Records for both NC045512 and MN908947.3 genomes which describe the exact or the approximate number of unaltered consecutive nucleotide sequences found in PCR cultures, as a percentage of the total genome size of 29,903. This number or percentage would exclude sequences derived by all other means including: - insertion of GenBank reference sequences - sequences derived by computer algorithms - consensus by panel To be clear, I am not requesting records which compare either published genome with any reference sequence(s), but rather, what portion of the 29,903 bases, for each of the two genomes specified above, represents unaltered nucleotide sequences as observed in the PCR amplicons. If no specific records for this request exist, an approximation by a CDC expert, with a brief explanation of the ratio, as a number or percentage, will suffice. (D (Date Range for Record Search: From 12/1/2019 To 1/8/2021)

request_text: Good afternoon, This is Maria Perez, a reporter with the Milwaukee Journal Sentinel. I’d like to make a public records request for any records pertaining to the CDC investigation about the circumstances in which a man died of COVID-19 in a commercial bus and why the commercial bus was transporting passengers with COVID-19. The bus, belonging the company El Tornado, departed on Oct. 13, 2020 form a Seneca Foods labor camp in Gillett, Wisconsin. It made a stop in Chicago, where it picked passengers not affiliated with the company, and then made another stop in Effingham, Illinois, that same day. A man,b6 died on the bus of COVID-19. His brother b6, another passenger of the bus, was hospitalized soon after his brother died and also tested positive for COVID-19. The same bus continued from Effingham to Dallas, where passengers boarded two separate buses heading to Laredo and McAllen. They arrived to their destinations on Oct. 14. At least another passenger of the bus,b6, would later die of COVID-19 in Laredo. [COVID-19] (Date Range for Record Search: From 10/13/2020 To 1/18/2021)

request_text: Dear CDC, My request is to see: All records in the possession, custody or control of the Centers of Disease Control describing the isolation of a SARS-COV-2 virus, directly from a sample taken from a diseased patient, where the patient sample was not first combined with any other source of genetic material (i.e. monkey kidney cells aka vero cells; liver cancer cells). Please note that I am using “isolation” in the every-day sense of the word: the act of separating a thing(s) from everything else. I am not requesting records where “isolation of SARS-COV-2” refers *instead* to: • the culturing of something, or • the performance of an amplification test (i.e. a PCR test), or • the sequencing of something. Please also note that my request is not limited to records that were authored by the CDC or that pertain to work done by the CDC. My request includes any sort of record, for example (but not limited to) any published peer-reviewed study that the CDC has downloaded or printed. Please provide enough information about each record so that I may identify and access each record with certainty (i.e. title, author(s), date, journal, where the public may access it).” Thank you, Jeff Jackson

request_text: Feb. 3, 2021 CDC/ATSDR FOIA Office 1600 Clifton Road, NE, Mailstop D54 Atlanta, Georgia 30333 To Whom It May Concern: Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request: The five (5) most recent spreadsheets, tables or other documents supplied to CDC, Operation Warp Speed or White House decision makers that are generated using data from the COVID-19 IZ Data Lake or the IZ Data Clearing House, post-deidentification, that include one or all of the following: COVID-19 vaccination rates by vaccination site/provider, census tract, zip code or county COVID-19 vaccination rates aggregated by race and/or age by vaccination site/provider, census tract, zip code or county If you determine that portions of a requested record are exempt from disclosure, please redact the exempt portions and provide the remainder of the record. request_text: request for a listing of site locations that are, known to be or suspected to be, contaminated with PFAS chemicals, for the entire state, in spreadsheet format. PFAS is a class of chemicals that includes PFOA (perfluorooctanoic acid), PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid), PFNA (perfluorononanoic acid) and PFHxA (perfluorohexanoic acid). PFOA and PFOS, are the most commonly found and potent PFASs at contamination sites. ATSDR is involved at a number of PFAS-related sites, either directly or through assisting state and federal partners. As of now, most sites are related to drinking water contamination connected with PFAS production facilities or fire training areas where aqueous film-forming firefighting foam (AFFF) was regularly used. We are working with one state partner on a site where consuming contaminated fish is the concern. Information I would like includes: Contamination site name Location address Location city Location state Location zip code Location county Latitude Longitude Name of source (s) Litigation (ues or no) PFOA or PFOS Other PFAS Date of discovery Suspected contamination source Suspected source url Notes Date Government response Community response Litigation details Agency site url

I certify that this information is true and correct to the best of my knowledge. (See Al-Fayed v. C.I.A., 254 F.3d 300, 310 (D.C. Cir. 2001); Bloomberg, L.P. v. U.S. Food & Drug Admin., 500 F.Supp.2d 371, 378 (S.D.N.Y. 2007). If you regard these documents as potentially exempt from the FOIA’s disclosure requirements, I request that you nonetheless exercise your discretion to disclose them. As the FOIA requires under 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(8), please release all segregable, non-exempt portions of documents. To permit me to reach an intelligent and informed decision whether to file an administrative appeal of any denied material, please describe any withheld records (or portions thereof) and explain the basis for your exemption claims. As required by the statute, please review whether there is any foreseeable harm from disclosing the requested records, or if any potential harm would be limited in comparison to the public interest in disclosure. As required by 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(8), please release all such information, even if it technically may fall under a FOIA exemption. request_text: I would like to request all documents related to the factual review process behind the CDC's website titled, "U.S. Public Health Service Syphilis Study at Tuskegee." On the website, the CDC notes, "This page is currently under review by CDC to ensure the content is accurate and verifiable." I would like all reports, memos, emails, and other electronic records of the fact-checking process behind these points published on the CDC website. This should include but not be limited to all questions and comments submitted to the CDC by outside sources regarding the points published online. Given the nature of this request, and how vital of a role this information is playing in the country's vaccination efforts for the Black or African-American community, I request expedited processing. If any part of this request is ambiguous or does not match the nomenclature of your agency, I would appreciate your cooperation and communication so I may narrow or adjust the requested description in order to facilitate your production with a minimum expense or disruption on your part, as required by state law. Please contact me if you have any questions regarding what I am requesting. If you determine that some but not all of the information are exempt from disclosure and that you intend to withhold it, I ask that you redact it for the time being and make the rest available as requested. In any event, please provide a signed notification citing the legal authorities on which you rely if you determine that any or all of the information is exempt and will not be disclosed. If some of these requested records are available for release before others, I ask that your agency release these records as they become available, while continuing to process this request. If I can provide any clarification that will help expedite your attention to my request, please contact me at (619) 618-9243. If the records I am requesting are not available in an electronic format, I ask that you notify me of any duplication costs exceeding $50 before you duplicate the records so that I may decide which records I want to be copied. Thank you for your commitment to serving the public interest through an open and transparent government process.

request_text: To Whom It May Concern: Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records: I am hereby requesting the following records that relate to Tiberius, a data organization software developed by Palantir designed to help "the federal government set up a system that will track the manufacture, distribution and administration of Covid-19 vaccines." Tiberius is a part of Operation Warp Speed. (https://www.wsj.com/articles/palantir-to-help-u-s-track-covid-19-vaccines-11603367276) 1) Any contracts, memorandums of understanding, purchase, orders, invoices, and receipts related to "Tiberius." These documents may be addressed directly to "Palantir" but should necessarily mention "Tiberius." 2) All instructional materials, presentations and presentation materials (including recorded video and audio, PowerPoint files, prepared remarks, and slides formats), and other guidance on the use of "Tiberius." This includes: A) any notes taken during meetings that discussed the use of "Tiberius." B) any explanations (whether internally or externally generated) of how "Tiberius" works. C) any other document that has been used to help explain the use of "Tiberius" to any party, including internal documentation, public relations materials, and executive summaries. Please limit the time frame of all searches to August 1, 2020 to the time that this request is processed. Also, please waive all fees associated with this request, since I am a member of the news media as a reporter for BuzzFeed News, and the requested documents are in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires. Sincerely, Caroline Haskins Upload documents directly: https://https://www.muckrock.comhttps://accounts.muckrock.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.muckrock.com%2Faccounts%2Flogin%2F%3Fnext%3D%252Faccounts%252Fagency_login%252Fcenter-for-disease-control-152%252Fvaccine-coordination-cell-109263%252F%253Femail%253Dfoiarequests%252540cdc.gov&url_auth_token=AABagxBJxEnp8bMIImfGZ311LoQ%3A1lJMQy%3ArdX_9KpIsXCJwv31MlKVij_SW4w (Date Range for Record Search: From 08/01/2020 To 03/08/2021)

request_text: Requesting non-personally identifying data collected by the agency through the V-Safe After Vaccination Health Checker. Specifically would like to have data provided in spreadsheet form with the following fields: "Vaccine Given" "Year of Birth" "Date of Vaccine" "Date of Check-in" "How are you feeling today" "Fever check" "Symptom check" and "Health impact." Would prefer to have data only from profiles with the ZIP code 27244 (in Elon, North Carolina), but that data can be expanded to all ZIP codes in Alamance County, North Carolina (27215, 27217, 27302, 27253, 27244, 27258, 27349, 27216, 27340, 27201, 27202, 27359, 27220) if a larger data set is required to protect personally identifiable information. Similarly, the goal of collecting data from "Date of Vaccine" and "Date of Report" is to understand the timing of symptoms being reported, so if the agency collects and prefers to instead simply report the time difference between the vaccination and the date of the report, that certainly satisfies the intent of this request. This request is for the timespan covering all data since the V-Safe program was launched until the receipt of this request.

request_text: 1) Has the SARS-CoV-2 virus been isolated in a lab? If not, why not? 2) 'from your website'...All RT-PCR tests for SARS-CoV-2 detect genetic material from the virus. However, among the available diagnostic RT-PCR tests, the nucleic acid target within the SARS-CoV-2 genome varies. Question/Request: explain in great detail for a layman what the statement "...the nucleic acid target within the SARS-CoV-2 genome varies." 3) 'from your website' There is a correlation between the Ct value and the amount of viral genetic material that was present in the specimen. Explain in great detail the correlation you write of. 4) What is the latest RT-PCR ct that CDC recommends to detect the SARS-CoV-2 virus? 5) Why use the RT-PCR test when the results are meaningless for the health and safety of the human population? Point in fact: you state on your website"a quantitative RT-PCR test cannot determine how much virus is present in an individual patient specimen" & "In a qualitative RT-PCR test, known amounts of virus are used during the development of the test to determine what Ct values are associated with positive and negative specimens. A Ct value is generated when testing a patient specimen. The Ct value is interpreted as positive or negative but cannot be used to determine how much virus is present in an individual patient specimen." 6) Why do you not stop the USA government from using the RT-PCR test to quarantine humans? from your website:"Ct values should not be used to determine a patient’s viral load, how infectious a person may be, or when a person can be released from isolation or quarantine." 7) How do you distinguish between a patients genome material and the SARS-CoV-2 virus material? from your website:"In addition to detecting SARS-CoV-2 genetic material, each RT-PCR diagnostic test also detects a small portion of a patient’s genome. Detecting the patient’s genetic material in the specimen confirms the quality of the specimen and the processing steps of the test. If the patient’s genetic material is detected, then we can be reasonably sure that the viral genetic material was not degraded, and the test result is accurate." Please respond to this request ASAP. These questions should be extremely simple for your scientists to answer. Thank you.
